args: Once upon a time, long, looong ago...\n(Okay, it wasn't THAT long ago, but whatever.)\nOne fated day, out in the woods, I met Luccy.

I was sobbing my eyes out, having lost my
mom and dad, and he swooped in to save me.
That's when love struck like a lightning bolt!
I just knew we were destined to be together.

Sure, fate conspired to keep us apart for some
time after that, but I never stopped searching
for him...until, at long last, we were reunited!
And on that special day, he had this to say:

＂Come and live with me in my castle.＂

SQUEEEEE! OHHH EMMM GEEE!
I CAN'T EVEN! LITERALLY! OR FIGURATIVELY!

Everything was going so smoothly it had me
hyperventilating! I was living under the same
roof as my love! And as those happy days
went on, the event I'd been waiting for was
finally upon us.

Yes... Valentine's Day had come at last!
There'd be gifts and dates and professions
of undying love! Our bond would grow even
deeper! So, to get things started...
LUCCY! Here you go: a super-special\nValentine's Day present, from me to you!
Yeaaah, uh... I'm not really sure where\nto even start with you this time.
Let's go with, ＂What are you wearing?＂\nAlso, you mentioned a present, but you're\nempty-handed. What gives?
Awww, silly Luccy! This dress is both\nthe gift box AND the big ol' bow on top!
And your present is...little ol' me!
Did I surprise you? Sorry if this\nis an eensy-weensy bit sudden!
Back up a sec. What's happening?\nBetter yet, WHY'S it happening?
Because it's Valentine's, silly! Don't you\nwanna take our love to the next level?
That's why I thought of the perfect present.\nWhen I asked myself what I most wanted\nto give you, the answer was simple: me!
You say that, but you completely lost me.\nWho the heck's ever heard of giving a\nperson as a present, anyway?
I dunnooo, but I'm all yours now, Luccy.\nOop, joy's flooding out of my nose\nlike a waterfall!
Chelsea, that's blood. And hey, are\nyou even listening to me? Wait. Dumb\nquestion. Of course you're not.
Eee hee hee! Now that I'm one of your\nbelongings, I get to come home with you!
I've gotta pick out the best vantage spot\nfor maximum Luccy-gazing. How about...\nhere? Ooh, or maybe here? No, wait, here!
I'll be right at your bedside so I can\nwatch you sleep aaaaall night long!
Wha—hey! Don't go building a nest outta\nmy pillows. I use those to sleep 'n stuff!
Oops! Sorry, Luccy. Am I in the way?\nI'll move so I'm across from the door, then!
Eeeee hee hee hee hee hee!
I give up. She's even more, uh...\n＂passionate＂ than usual today.
Thank you, Luca. Do you have everything\nwith you? You always take off in such a\nhurry that I worry you'll forget something.
Aw, I'm fine! Got my bow, plenty of arrows,\nand even a buncha apples to snack on.\nI'm not leaving anything—
Like ME, silly! It's imperative that you\nkeep me on your person at all times.
Wow, yeah, completely slipped my mind...\nMaybe because that's NOT HAPPENING!
*sigh* But of course you came with me\nanyway.
Tee hee! I won't stand for you leaving\nhome without me, mister!
Look, how am I supposed to patrol properly\nwith you clinging to me like some kinda\nland-barnacle? I've gotta move, y'know!
Wait up, Luccy! If you go too far,\nsomeone's liable to come scoop me\nup and drop me at the lost-and-found!
If only. Now c'mon, I'm trying to walk\nhere! Quit goofing around and let's go.
You make the whole ＂gruff, bossy hubby＂\nthing work for you, Luccy. Hee hee.\nJust lead the way and I shall follow!
Phew. Finally finished my patrol.\nWhere'd my number one fan run off to?
HOLY...!\nHow are you back in my room before me?
Why, because I'm yours, silly!\nIt's only natural for me to be here.
Chelsea. Please.\nCan we drop this whole bit?
About you being my present,\nor some object that ＂belongs＂ to me.
You're a grown woman, Chelsea.\nPeople aren't commodities to own.
Awww, but Luccy... What am I supposed\nto give you for Valentine's Day, then?
I don't care, as long as it's something\nnormal! Emphasis on ＂thing.＂
A thing...\nSo that's what you want.
Right. And that does NOT include you. I'm\nsure anything you pick out will be great.
That's so sweet, Luccy. Okay! I'll keep\nbrainstorming the perfect present, then.
*mumble mumble grumble rumble...*\n*mumble grumble rumble mumble...*\nNnnnngrrrgh...
I can't sleep! The more I think about what\nI wanna give Luccy, the more ideas come\nto mind.
I can't pick only one.\nI wish I could just...give him all of them.
Waaait a second. Silly me.\nThat's EXACTLY what I'll do!
Eee hee hee, Valentine's Day is juuust\ngetting started. We're for SURE going on\na date and pledging our eternal love.
But first, I'll make my feelings clear with\na whole heap of presents. Prepare to be\npositively showered with affection, Luccy!
Lots and lots and lots and lots and lots and\nLOTS and LOTS and LOTS and LOTS and\nLOTS AND LOTS AND LOTS AND LOTS of it!
It'll be less a shower of affection...\nand more of a HURRICANE! Hee hee!
